    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1783"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/56.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your August 14. You are instructed to convey to the Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    the gratification of this Government at the prompt manner in which Panama
                    acceded to the request of the United States for control of radio communication.
                    Department desires duplicate copies and translation of decree of Panaman
                    President granting this control.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
